    "The first approach, integrating citations directly from LLM's parametric knowledge, poses a significant technical challenge.",
    "Unlike search engines and IR systems that rely on indices for data retrieval, LLMs encode information into hidden representations during training, lacking a direct index.",
    "Therefore, referencing the sources of information becomes intricate.",
    "Despite these challenges, approaches have been suggested to train LLMs to include references using source identifiers (Taylor et al., 2022).",
    "However, these methods exhibit certain limitations, including citation inaccuracies and being restricted to academic citations."
